Sample Amazon Review Analysis - Data Analytics

I have done a sample Amazon review analysis using R and published it as HTML file.

Data Source: https://www.kaggle.com/datafiniti/consumer-reviews-of-amazon-products.

The program processes the reviews and highlights the most used words as well as computes the average rating for top manufacturers

Extracting the title

CleanedPro_C <- Corpus (VectorSource(AData$reviews.title))

Cleaning the text

toSpace <- content_transformer(function (x , pattern ) gsub(pattern, " ", x))
CleanedPro_C <- tm_map(CleanedPro_C, toSpace, "/")
CleanedPro_C <- tm_map(CleanedPro_C, toSpace, "@")
CleanedPro_C <- tm_map(CleanedPro_C, toSpace, "\\|")
CleanedPro_C <- tm_map(CleanedPro_C, removeNumbers)

Processing the words

dtm <- TermDocumentMatrix(CleanedPro_C)
m <- as.matrix(dtm)
v <- sort(rowSums(m),decreasing=TRUE)
d <- data.frame(word = names(v),freq_pro=v)

Amazon Reviews WordCloud

wordcloud(words = d$word, freq = d$freq_pro, min.freq = 1,
          max.words=500, random.order=FALSE, rot.per=0.35, 
          colors=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"))

Top Amazon Manufacturer from Reviews Ratings

AData1 %>%
  group_by(manufacturer)%>%
  summarise(Ratings = mean(reviews.rating, na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x=manufacturer, y = Ratings))+
  geom_col()
